    "description": "NIC Autotec, Inc. manufacture and sells aluminum frame and FA equipment in Japan and internationally. It offers alpha frame system; alpha clean system; aluminum stand for small robots; alpha guard safety fence; alpha kit, aquarium stands, and server racks; and cup-type washing machine/blow machine. The company also provides FA equipment, including washing machines for batch type and individual cleaning; conveyors comprising automatic cartoners, palletizing stackers, free-flow conveyors, and other various conveyors; screening inspection equipment for dimensions, tap failure, running torque, etc.; and cleanroom products. It serves FA equipment for use in machining factories, semi-conductor and electronic parts factories, and pharmaceutical and food factories. The company was formerly known as Nishikawa Seiki Inc. and changed its name to NIC Autotec, Inc. in April 1985. NIC Autotec, Inc. was founded in 1927 and is headquartered in Toyama, Japan."
